What are Thrust Spherical Roller Bearings?
Thrust spherical roller bearings are heavy-duty rolling bearings specifically engineered to withstand extremely high axial loads while simultaneously accommodating moderate radial loads and shaft misalignment. Their unique design combines spherical raceways with asymmetrical rollers, allowing automatic self-alignment of up to 2–3 degrees, significantly improving operational reliability even under demanding industrial conditions.
These bearings are widely used in steel mills, mining equipment, marine propulsion systems, construction machinery, hydroelectric plants, wind turbines, cement manufacturing, and other heavy industrial applications where durability, high load capacity, and long service life are essential.
